  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nDealers are currently buying the dip as SPX sits 27 points below the flip at 6587, with massive positive gamma walls at 6580 (+30.5B) and 6570 (+22.2B) creating strong upside resistance that will trigger dealer selling into any rally attempt. The PIN regime combined with the recent GEX surge suggests dealers are aggressively hedging long gamma positions, which should cap upside momentum and pull price back toward the 6580 max gamma strike. Watch for dealer buying support to strengthen near 6550 (-24.5B negative gamma) if we break lower, but expect mean reversion back toward 6580 given the current stabilizing gamma profile.",
